    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Oil Cooler and Filter Housing - Installation - Oil Filter Base and Housing
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="6">
        <title>Oil Filter Base and Housing</title>
        <figure id="e3001030" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ13/J13039.cgm" type="cgm" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Latching return tube</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Latching return tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Latching return tube gasket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter housing</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate a new latching return tube gasket with clean engine oil and install onto latching
                return tube.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001031" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ13/J13037.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the latching return tube</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install latching return tube by pushing down and twisting tube 120&#176; clockwise until
                latched.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001032" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ13/J13040.cgm" type="cgm" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="408px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil filter base and housing details</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Screw, (M6 x 25)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter base</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter housing gasket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter housing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil drain valve assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Latching return tube assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter element</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter cap seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter cap</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new oil filter housing gasket between the housing and base.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install six oil filter housing mounting bolts (M6 x 25). Tighten bolts to the
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_203.xml" xrefid="E30010B" appearance="hottext">Special Torque</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001033" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj13/J13041.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil filter housing assembly to engine</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Stud bolt, M8 x 50 x 16 (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 50</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position oil filter housing onto oil filter adapter and intake manifold. Tighten bolts to
                the
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_311.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">Standard Torque</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001034" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj11/J11024.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the oil filter and cap assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="e3001035" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj11/J11025.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the oil filter cap</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil filter and cap as a combined unit. Tighten cap to the
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_203.xml" xrefid="E30010B" appearance="hottext">Special Torque</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, add oil to the engine before starting. Also, see your Engine Operation
                    and Maintenance Manual for engine oil and filter service interval. Proper maintenance of your engine
                    will prolong service life.
                </para>
            </caution>
            <caution>
                <para>The correct oil viscosity for diesel engines is important for satisfactory operation, especially
                    in cold weather. Follow the chart in the Engine Operation and Maintenance Manual to determine which
                    oil viscosity is best suited for the temperature range you expect to encounter.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fill crankcase with oil. See the Operation and Maintenance Manual for correct refill
                capacity.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Engine fluids, oil, fuel, and coolant, can be a threat to the environment. Never dispose of
                        engine fluids by putting them in the trash, pouring them on the ground, in sewers, streams or
                        bodies of water.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Start engine and check for leaks. Correct any leakage as necessary. Shut down engine and
                check engine oil level. Add oil or drain oil as needed to bring oil level to the FULL mark on oil level
                gauge. Do not overfill past the FULL mark.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
